Issuer Purchases of Equity Securities
In March 2011, our Board of Directors approved a stock repurchase program, pursuant to which we are authorized to
repurchase up to $1.5 billion of our common stock (the “2011 Buyback”). In addition to the 2011 Buyback, in December 2017, our
Board of Directors approved an additional stock repurchase program, pursuant to which we are authorized to repurchase up to $2.0
billion of our common stock (the “2017 Buyback”, and together with the 2011 Buyback the “Buyback Programs”).
During the three months ended December 31, 2019, we repurchased a total of 93,654 shares of our common stock for an
aggregate of $19.6 million, including commissions and fees, pursuant to the 2011 Buyback. There were no repurchases under the
2017 Buyback. The table below sets forth details of our repurchases under the 2011 Buyback during the three months ended
