Functional Currency—The functional currency of each of the Company’s foreign operating subsidiaries is normally the respective
local currency, except for Costa Rica and Argentina, where the functional currency is the U.S. Dollar. All foreign currency assets
and liabilities held by the subsidiaries are translated into U.S. Dollars at the exchange rate in effect at the end of the applicable
fiscal reporting period and all foreign currency revenues and expenses are translated at the average monthly exchange rates.
Translation adjustments are reflected in equity as a component of Accumulated other comprehensive loss
